Unilever Buys ‘Green’ Products Maker Seventh Generation    
Unilever to pay roughly $700 million for Seventh Generation, a source said 

 






By

Saabira Chaudhuri and 
              

Saabira Chaudhuri
The Wall Street Journal
BiographySaabira Chaudhuri
@saabirac
Google+
Saabira.Chaudhuri@wsj.com



Sharon Terlep


Sharon Terlep
The Wall Street Journal
BiographySharon Terlep
@sharonterlep





  Updated Sept. 19, 2016 4:47 p.m. ET





LONDON—Unilever PLC is getting into the market for “natural” cleaning products with a deal to buy Seventh Generation Inc., a maker of plant-based detergents and household cleaners.  The European consumer products giant behind Dove soaps and Axe body sprays agreed to pay roughly $700 million for Seventh Generation, a person familiar with the...
  


